This extension for RubyMine IDE provides simple Zen-Conding (http://code.google.com/p/zen-coding/) snippets support.

----------
Requirements:

* RubyMine  >= 2.0.1 rc2

----------
Installation:

1. $ cd [your_favorite_directory]
   $ git clone git://github.com/iromeo/zen-coding-rm-plugin.git zen-conding-rm-plugin
   $ cd zen-conding-rm-plugin
   $ svn checkout http://zen-coding.googlecode.com/svn/trunk zen-coding-read-only

2. If you are using Ubuntu or MacOS go to 3)

   For Windows users:
   * Install python
   * Specify path to python executable in [your_favorite_directory]/zen-conding-rm-plugin/config.yml file

3. * Launch RubyMine
   * Open File | Settings | Extensions" dialog
   * Press "Add" button and specify [your_favorite_directory]/zen-conding-rm-plugin/ext folder
   * Press "Apply"
   * Relaunch RubyMine. 

-------
How To Use:
  1. Open erb, html, xml or css file in RubyMine
  2. E.g. type "div#sales>div+div.sales_header+div.sales_body+div.sales_footer" in editor
  3. Press Ctrl+Shift+J (or Tools | Extensions | Expand Zen-Coding Template)

-------
Support:
  Ask any questions on RubyMine official forum - http://www.jetbrains.net/devnet/community/ruby
